Heat a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat and once hot, add the @diced chicken thighs{260%g}. Fry for ~{10%minutes}, stirring often.

Meanwhile, trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways then thinly slice widthways.

Add the @coleslaw mix{120%g} to a #small bowl{} with the @red wine vinegar{12%ml} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Set aside.

Add half the @chipotle paste{20%g} and the @low fat natural yoghurt{150%g} to another small bowl, season and mix well.

Place the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} on a large lightly oiled #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{a drizzle} and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Bake on the top shelf of the #oven{} until crispy, ~{3-4%minutes}. Keep an eye on them to avoid burning! These are your tostadas.

Once the chicken has had 10 mins in the pan and is cooked through, reduce the heat to medium, stir in the @easy garlic{1} along with the remaining chipotle paste and let cook for a final ~{3%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

> TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Grab the tostadas from the oven and pile up one tostada per person on plates with the baby gem lettuce, coleslaw, chipotle garlic chicken and chipotle yoghurt.

Dig in to the tostadas and have the remaining food ready for round two!